      "text": "Sit on the bike while someone holds and pushes you at a walking pace. Turn the pedals so that you feel pressure in your toes all the way around. Push a little harder. Feel more pressure. Now harder still. As you go faster your helper will be getting tired. Press harder still and ride away alone."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
